  "text": "Currently, about 55 % of fossil fuel carbon emissions are removed from the atmosphere by a suite of terrestrial and oceanic processes with uptake rates governed by factors such as climate variability and changes in land cover [CITATION_1] ). The remaining CO 2 -the so called \"airborne fraction\" -is a key metric of both the anthropogenic contribution to global warming and a top-down estimate of all carbon-cycle processes.",
